        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"David_Bolt\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"72524\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/david_bolt/48/54424_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> David_Bolt:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Explore a ‚Äúvoice-to-text / text-to-voice</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Signal already has voice notes. That should easily solve for this, and the general calling problem.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"David_Bolt\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"72524\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/david_bolt/48/54424_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> David_Bolt:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Allow users to opt out of fixed, continuous voice packets when bandwidth</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Have you tried turning on ‚Äúalways route calls through server‚Äù? The issue might be that the P2P connection is too weak, so routing through the server might be a quicker solution.</p>",
